</taxonomicName>
L.f., 
<taxonomicName id="DF67AA7201B629CC56B0758A04499BEF" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Morinda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Morinda citrifolia" order="Gentianales" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="citrifolia">
<emphasis id="1D656AE63B9C5188E7A2E0F0175A3EA8" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">Morinda citrifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName id="61D8F8E210A1C1DF61D3F4D9875D9379" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Pandanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pandanus macrocarpus" order="Pandanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="macrocarpus">
<emphasis id="49E5A08C438A4F754CB1E93EF3695142" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">Pandanus macrocarpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Brongn.) Solms, 
<taxonomicName id="BE27821BB3DE9AED9FCAC025FB05D617" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Podonephelium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Podonephelium homei" order="Sapindales" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="homei">
<emphasis id="69E4245D5F8C62C5F784411035BE87DF" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">Podonephelium homei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Seem.) Radlk., 
<taxonomicName id="21E0F252907BB6514AA37578DB62544D" authority="(R. Vig.) Lowry subsp. bracteata" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Araliaceae" genus="Polyscias" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Polyscias bracteata subsp. bracteata" order="Umbelliflorae" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="subSpecies" species="bracteata" subSpecies="bracteata">Polyscias bracteata (R.Vig.) Lowry subsp. bracteata</taxonomicName>
., 
<taxonomicName id="05D8AA97FE103A9B4F1110F391806881" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Psidium" higherTaxonomySource="IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Psidium guajava" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="guajava">
<emphasis id="2DDB9B1B181920FC443DED44493338A5" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">Psidium guajava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., and 
<taxonomicName id="D436167A5C40D1FBBF56924C9D6B953A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Schinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Schinus terebenthifolius" order="Sapindales" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="terebenthifolius">
<emphasis id="02F366A3A94EFB8BA9F0BAE9EA16F7C7" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">Schinus terebenthifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Raddi. Loyalty sandalwood is a hemiparasitic tree like all 
<taxonomicName id="A13915BEE0F2FD0E31F4381BB64F5721" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Santalaceae" genus="Santalum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Santalum" order="Santalales" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6845755D5F8832F131CD82A44BB01D81" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">Santalum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species; its pollination is insect-mediated whereas its fleshy fruits are dispersed mainly by doves and pigeons (
<bibRefCitation id="1E4B5D2DF49BD923DC1312CAAA615900" author="Bottin, L" journalOrPublisher="Molecular ecology" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" pagination="1979 - 1989" publicationUrl="10.1111/j.1365-294X.2005.02576.x" refId="B3" refString="Bottin, L, Verhaegen, D, Tassin, J, Olivieri, I, Vaillant, A, Bouvet, JM, 2005. Genetic diversity and population structure of an insular tree Santalum austrocaledonicum in New Caledonia archipelago. Molecular ecology 14: 1979 - 1989, DOI: 10.1111/j.1365-294X.2005.02576.x" title="Genetic diversity and population structure of an insular tree Santalum austrocaledonicum in New Caledonia archipelago." url="10.1111/j.1365-294X.2005.02576.x" volume="14" year="2005">Bottin et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F25AE245441E44C1BEADAD885E330CBE" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="115" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="D070003518618A3B97C6C992F2DEC1B6" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5199A06E119D2AE4691D060A499F3AF9" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="115" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">
Using the categories and criteria of 
<bibRefCitation id="A775C3DEFB94777F3672931128C94B13" author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="IUCN Species Survival Commission, Gland, Switzerland" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/info/categories_criteria2001" refId="B17" refString="IUCN, 2001. IUCN Red List categories (version 3.1). IUCN Species Survival Commission, Gland, Switzerland, http://www.iucnredlist.org/info/categories_criteria2001" title="IUCN Red List categories (version 3.1)" url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/info/categories_criteria2001" year="2001">IUCN (2001)</bibRefCitation>
, we propose for 
<taxonomicName id="78EECA9F6176F2CBD1739E85C815B88C" authorityName="Huerl. emend. Butaud &amp; P. Firmenich" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Santalaceae" genus="Santalum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Santalum austrocaledonicum subsp. var. var. glabrum" order="Santalales" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="austrocaledonicum" subSpecies="var." variety="glabrum">Santalum austrocaledonicum var. glabrum</taxonomicName>
the IUCN Red List Category Vulnerable (VU): B (1+2) ab (iii,v). Its population size is estimated at more than 10,000 mature individuals (excluding criteria C and D) with an extent of occurrence around 8,000 km² and an area of occupancy around 1,000 km². Criteria A can not be used due to 
<pageBreakToken id="66EA93890CEDD2B174E0C200EE8EB545" pageId="4" pageNumber="115" start="start">lack</pageBreakToken>
of knowledge of generation length and magnitude of population size reduction. Three locations (one per island) can be distinguished without any fragmentation. A continuing decline is observed and projected in terms of habitat quality and number of mature individuals due to harvest, competition with invasive plant species (
<taxonomicName id="5A63A77EE5A783DBCE23202D5EA29012" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Schinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Schinus terebenthifolius" order="Sapindales" pageId="4" pageNumber="115" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="terebenthifolius">
<emphasis id="726419700EA339C74D206DDB5E50339D" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="115">Schinus terebenthifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Raddi, 
<taxonomicName id="EC76FE45CA11BEA1DC200D62F2F67F6E" authorityName="Cass" authorityYear="1826" baseAuthorityName="L." class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Asteraceae" genus="Pluchea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pluchea odorata" order="Campanulales" pageId="4" pageNumber="115" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="odorata">
<emphasis id="8AF9939A4EEA7C6079763BBA8219D421" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="115">Pluchea odorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Cass., 
<taxonomicName id="77507479EE68121474AF32F095F5C252" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Lantana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lantana camara" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="4" pageNumber="115" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="camara">
<emphasis id="9B9F4546B69223A7B4511185C6CEC862" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="115">Lantana camara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.), hybridization with other 
<taxonomicName id="CEC625EBDF65C6E0F44D87081DE0DD0C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Santalaceae" genus="Santalum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Santalum austrocaledonicum" order="Santalales" pageId="4" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="austrocaledonicum">
<emphasis id="50497CA26708E334F6870BA84C19B399" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="115">Santalum austrocaledonicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
varieties used in plantations, and changes in the traditional agricultural system (less cultivated fields, short fallows...). Indeed, despite provincial regulations establishing quota and exploitability criteria, illegal logging is still occurring (
<bibRefCitation id="0595761AE4F8212FC89E94D161C56D63" author="Butaud, JF" journalOrPublisher="Conservation International &amp; Province des Iles Loyaute" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 370" refId="B7" refString="Butaud, JF, Guy, L, Lefeuvre, JC, 2013. Etude sur l'etat de la ressource naturelle en santal aux Iles Loyaute pour le developpement de filieres aromatiques certifiees. Conservation International &amp; Province des Iles Loyaute: 1 - 370" title="Etude sur l'etat de la ressource naturelle en santal aux Iles Loyaute pour le developpement de filieres aromatiques certifiees" year="2013">Butaud et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
) whereas hybridization is suspected due to sandalwood interspecific crossability (
<bibRefCitation id="35A711A4EAA91C034640883E50C2B972" author="Tamla, HT" journalOrPublisher="Euphytica" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" pagination="323 - 333" publicationUrl="10.1007/s10681-011-0530-y" refId="B28" refString="Tamla, HT, Cornelius, JP, Page, T, 2012. Reproductive biology of three commercially valuable Santalum species: development of flowers and inflorescences, breeding systems, and interspecific crossability. Euphytica 184: 323 - 333, DOI: 10.1007/s10681-011-0530-y" title="Reproductive biology of three commercially valuable Santalum species: development of flowers and inflorescences, breeding systems, and interspecific crossability." url="10.1007/s10681-011-0530-y" volume="184" year="2012">Tamla et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DD96D24548A53B87773C270276DD8C96" pageId="4" pageNumber="115" type="common names">
<paragraph id="C15D85C787A07F744837F2A28812B072" pageId="4" pageNumber="115">Common names.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E73D524024A652951976158CFDE443C" pageId="4" pageNumber="115">
The common names recorded for 
<taxonomicName id="47AC21F486FCF6DE3BAA7C364EDAFEA1" authorityName="Huerl. emend. Butaud &amp; P. Firmenich" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Santalaceae" genus="Santalum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Santalum austrocaledonicum subsp. var. var. glabrum" order="Santalales" pageId="4" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="austrocaledonicum" subSpecies="var." variety="glabrum">Santalum austrocaledonicum var. glabrum</taxonomicName>
are 
<normalizedToken id="1B50889E100A63B5C6799BEEFF1410DA" originalValue="“tapakae”">&quot;tapakae&quot;</normalizedToken>
(pers. obs. 2014) or 
<normalizedToken id="24D326A49A8B88A20F050B608A3378F7" originalValue="“tapakai”">&quot;tapakai&quot;</normalizedToken>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A436FB4C56A819E3D0F3FEA4DC707AF1" author="Lenormand, MH" journalOrPublisher="Journal d'Agriculture Tropicale et de Botanique Appliquee" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" pagination="173 - 194" publicationUrl="10.3406/jatba.1968.2979" refId="B18" refString="Lenormand, MH, 1968. Vocabulaire des noms de plantes medicinales et alimentaires utilisees par les Melanesiens de Lifou (Iles Loyalty). Journal d'Agriculture Tropicale et de Botanique Appliquee 15 (4-5-6): 173 - 194, DOI: 10.3406/jatba.1968.2979" title="Vocabulaire des noms de plantes medicinales et alimentaires utilisees par les Melanesiens de Lifou (Iles Loyalty)." url="10.3406/jatba.1968.2979" volume="15" year="1968">Lenormand 1968</bibRefCitation>
) on Lifou, 
<normalizedToken id="B659EBF14769317378DE76D7BC0CE0EE" originalValue="“wekesi”">&quot;wekesi&quot;</normalizedToken>
(
<bibRefCitation id="C8C0098B476B4D86C52FF8AB0AADD0F0" author="Lormee, N" journalOrPublisher="IRD Editions" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 358" refId="B19" refString="Lormee, N, Cabalion, P, Hnawia, ES, 2011. Hommes et plantes de Mare, iles Loyaute, Nouvelle-Caledonie. IRD Editions: 1 - 358" title="Hommes et plantes de Mare, iles Loyaute, Nouvelle-Caledonie" year="2011">
<normalizedToken id="74A15192A64E627A464E5E40FD3E0E94" originalValue="Lormée">Lormee</normalizedToken>
et al. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
) on 
<normalizedToken id="31D6F3B67A5E70A53DF4297AB6B816F1" originalValue="Maré">Mare</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="8A047C37EBE24D54D8A6E6B97DA71E86" originalValue="“wahata”">&quot;wahata&quot;</normalizedToken>
(
<bibRefCitation id="7F8BE4B3FFFF1081CCA555CA6E8D473C" author="Ozanne-Rivierre, F" journalOrPublisher="CNRS, Ivry-sur-Seine, France" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 181" refId="B24" refString="Ozanne-Rivierre, F, 1984. Dictionnaire Iaai - Francais (Ouvea Nouvelle-Caledonie) suivi d'un lexique francais-iaai. Laboratoire de langues et civilisations a tradition orale. CNRS, Ivry-sur-Seine, France: 1 - 181" title="Dictionnaire Iaai - Francais (Ouvea Nouvelle-Caledonie) suivi d'un lexique francais-iaai. Laboratoire de langues et civilisations a tradition orale" year="1984">Ozanne-Rivierre 1984</bibRefCitation>
) on 
<normalizedToken id="3585A65C756BB5DF095F835E2FCF4148" originalValue="Ouvéa">Ouvea</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BB493D1C0C3646E7F41A7946DDE8637B" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="116" pageId="4" pageNumber="115" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="CEFD5E45D2972FC9C2B7667088532E7C" pageId="4" pageNumber="115">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB292E7D818DC38391BBB68BF493CB7F" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="116" pageId="4" pageNumber="115">
<taxonomicName id="9E9C946E7E7D79B5189C03822FAE7EF7" authorityName="Huerl. emend. Butaud &amp; P. Firmenich" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Santalaceae" genus="Santalum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Santalum austrocaledonicum subsp. var. var. glabrum" order="Santalales" pageId="4" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="austrocaledonicum" subSpecies="var." variety="glabrum">Santalum austrocaledonicum var. glabrum</taxonomicName>
is the sole native sandalwood in the Loyalty Islands. Nevertheless, two other varieties have been introduced for plantation purposes, mainly in 
<normalizedToken id="69A8D529ACEEEA2C0897033F66FCE15B" originalValue="Maré">Mare</normalizedToken>
and Lifou: 
<taxonomicName id="92B64F9F4D22B0F9577EA8C18A5E6E6C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Santalaceae" genus="Santalum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. var. var. pilosulum" order="Santalales" pageId="4" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="austrocaledonicum" subSpecies="var." variety="pilosulum">var. pilosulum</taxonomicName>
from Ouen Toro in 
<normalizedToken id="B3FED4C6D799DEEFA4900D7D1C60C0AE" originalValue="Nouméa">Noumea</normalizedToken>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="F2C187118C9647961F3B6850A28EB7F4" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Santalaceae" genus="Santalum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. var. var. austrocaledonicum" order="Santalales" pageId="4" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="austrocaledonicum" subSpecies="var." variety="austrocaledonicum">var. austrocaledonicum</taxonomicName>
from Isle of Pines. These plantations can be considered a risk for the Loyalty variety because of hybridization and subsequent introgression. Plantations with exotic varieties should be discouraged to preserve the 
<pageBreakToken id="6C1ADBE9F6921BAF946EBE0B0C916CC6" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" start="start">Loyalty</pageBreakToken>
<normalizedToken id="18FA26C08D75197178692157CF17D70A" originalValue="sandalwood’s">sandalwood's</normalizedToken>
morphological, genetic, sylvicultural and chemical specificities (
<bibRefCitation id="AB79F9B70CFAD88AD7E67C6E76F151DB" author="Bottin, L" journalOrPublisher="ENSAM - CIRAD, Montpellier, France" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" refId="B1" refString="Bottin, L, 2006. Determinants de la variation moleculaire et phenotypique d'une espece forestiere en milieu insulaire : cas de Santalum austrocaledonicum en Nouvelle-Caledonie. ENSAM - CIRAD, Montpellier, France" title="Determinants de la variation moleculaire et phenotypique d'une espece forestiere en milieu insulaire: cas de Santalum austrocaledonicum en Nouvelle-Caledonie" year="2006">Bottin 2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EA3F7077B2BB6402E9E958A9B7248D0D" author="Bottin, L" journalOrPublisher="Conservation genetics" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" pagination="99 - 109" publicationUrl="10.1007/s10592-006-9152-7" refId="B2" refString="Bottin, L, Tassin, J, Nasi, R, Bouvet, JM, 2007. Molecular, quantitative and abiotic variables for the delineation of evolutionary significant units: case of sandalwood (Santalum austrocaledonicum Vieillard) in New Caledonia. Conservation genetics 8 (1): 99 - 109, DOI: 10.1007/s10592-006-9152-7" title="Molecular, quantitative and abiotic variables for the delineation of evolutionary significant units: case of sandalwood (Santalum austrocaledonicum Vieillard) in New Caledonia." url="10.1007/s10592-006-9152-7" volume="8" year="2007">Bottin et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="846C971B1FD55CAFC2F5A5AF68A3D8AC" author="Butaud, JF" journalOrPublisher="Conservation International &amp; Province des Iles Loyaute" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 370" refId="B7" refString="Butaud, JF, Guy, L, Lefeuvre, JC, 2013. Etude sur l'etat de la ressource naturelle en santal aux Iles Loyaute pour le developpement de filieres aromatiques certifiees. Conservation International &amp; Province des Iles Loyaute: 1 - 370" title="Etude sur l'etat de la ressource naturelle en santal aux Iles Loyaute pour le developpement de filieres aromatiques certifiees" year="2013">Butaud et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EE39B6C998E7C741ACA666C0D67B780D" author="Ehrhart, Y" editor="Radomiljac, AM" journalOrPublisher="ACIAR" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" pagination="113 - 116" refId="B9" refString="Ehrhart, Y, 1998. Description of some sandal tree populations in the South West Pacific: consequences for the silviculture of these species and provenances. In: Radomiljac, AM, Ananthapadmanabho, HS, Welbourn, RM, Satyanarayana Rao, K, Eds., Sandal and its products. ACIAR: 113 - 116" title="Description of some sandal tree populations in the South West Pacific: consequences for the silviculture of these species and provenances." volumeTitle="Sandal and its products." year="1998">Ehrhart 1998</bibRefCitation>
). On the other hand, the sustainable exploitation of natural stands of Loyalty Islands sandalwood is becoming increasingly difficult with the lack of regeneration and the increasing international demand for sandalwood essential oil. Well-managed plantations with 
<taxonomicName id="1E461B7AC79A2568FD54DA10B045987D" authorityName="Huerl. emend. Butaud &amp; P. Firmenich" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Santalaceae" genus="Santalum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. variety var. glabrum" order="Santalales" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="austrocaledonicum" subSpecies="variety" variety="glabrum">variety glabrum</taxonomicName>
could be promoted to preserve the natural stands, to develop the Loyalty sandalwood sector, and to increase the production of heartwood and essential oil (
<bibRefCitation id="DF45728DF402EFF2A5429D0FE0558DC5" author="Butaud, JF" journalOrPublisher="Nouvelle-Caledonie" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 238" refId="B6" refString="Butaud, JF, 2011. Analyse bibliographique et technique des references existantes sur le santal en vue de sa valorisation economique en plantations a l'echelle de la Nouvelle-Caledonie. In: IAC - Programme Foret Seche. Nouvelle-Caledonie: 1 - 238" title="Analyse bibliographique et technique des references existantes sur le santal en vue de sa valorisation economique en plantations a l'echelle de la Nouvelle-Caledonie" volumeTitle="IAC - Programme Foret Seche." year="2011">Butaud 2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="75D7DC85189C2FABB80975DBB563426C" author="Butaud, JF" journalOrPublisher="Conservation International &amp; Province des Iles Loyaute" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 370" refId="B7" refString="Butaud, JF, Guy, L, Lefeuvre, JC, 2013. Etude sur l'etat de la ressource naturelle en santal aux Iles Loyaute pour le developpement de filieres aromatiques certifiees. Conservation International &amp; Province des Iles Loyaute: 1 - 370" title="Etude sur l'etat de la ressource naturelle en santal aux Iles Loyaute pour le developpement de filieres aromatiques certifiees" year="2013">Butaud et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7FA3E69E692D37240BECBFAFE6F39EF9" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">
The taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName id="4AA38DE9B4AE0E3B57F595BC34077354" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Santalaceae" genus="Santalum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Santalum austrocaledonicum" order="Santalales" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="austrocaledonicum">
<emphasis id="0B626359282784D6CE146C94BE6AD326" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">Santalum austrocaledonicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
still needs to be further investigated. Indeed, the study of herbarium samples of 
<taxonomicName id="453515F39C49F30EA14798EB5D8C5A27" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Santalaceae" genus="Santalum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. var. var. austrocaledonicum" order="Santalales" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="austrocaledonicum" subSpecies="var." variety="austrocaledonicum">var. austrocaledonicum</taxonomicName>
and previous molecular and morphometric studies (
<bibRefCitation id="E0575A4DD8115CF0CCCC027978989D13" author="Bottin, L" journalOrPublisher="ENSAM - CIRAD, Montpellier, France" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" refId="B1" refString="Bottin, L, 2006. Determinants de la variation moleculaire et phenotypique d'une espece forestiere en milieu insulaire : cas de Santalum austrocaledonicum en Nouvelle-Caledonie. ENSAM - CIRAD, Montpellier, France" title="Determinants de la variation moleculaire et phenotypique d'une espece forestiere en milieu insulaire: cas de Santalum austrocaledonicum en Nouvelle-Caledonie" year="2006">Bottin 2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="48FC77DF8581A210E0D14E38678AB3F9" author="Bouvet, JM" editor="Thomson, L" journalOrPublisher="Noumea, New Caledonia" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" pagination="124 - 134" refId="B4" refString="Bouvet, JM, Cardi, C, Verhaegen, D, Butaud, JF, Nasi, R, Tassin, J, 2005. Molecular and morphometric diversity in Santalum insulare and Santalum austrocaledonicum. In: Thomson, L, Bulai, S, Sovea, L, Eds., Proceedings of the regional workshop on sandalwood research, development and extension in the Pacific islands and Asia. Noumea, New Caledonia: 124 - 134" title="Molecular and morphometric diversity in Santalum insulare and Santalum austrocaledonicum." volumeTitle="Proceedings of the regional workshop on sandalwood research, development and extension in the Pacific islands and Asia." year="2005">Bouvet et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
) showed significant variability. It is expected that future work supported by increased surveys and sampling of northern Grande-Terre sandalwood could reveal one or two new varieties, including one on Isle of Pines (taxon previously described as 
<taxonomicName id="B6222DC2751930ED5007774D366BA9EA" authorityName="Seem" authorityYear="1867" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Santalaceae" genus="Santalum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Santalum homei" order="Santalales" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="homei">
<emphasis id="0CB1EECE1B0653C6AC7C1C2A0BE67406" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">Santalum homei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Seem.). Moreover, two new endemic varieties of 
<taxonomicName id="61007C272173EBE3C0D57D8EE6128F03" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Santalaceae" genus="Santalum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Santalum austrocaledonicum" order="Santalales" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="austrocaledonicum">
<emphasis id="2751B0F628B03D17897D88D2AAEA7417" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">Santalum austrocaledonicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are expected based on the recent study of 
<bibRefCitation id="5003B404346B9853FD124B001635D54E" author="Millet, L" journalOrPublisher="Institut Agronomique neo-Caledonien &amp; Centre Technique et de Recherche en Agronomie du Vanuatu" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 41" refId="B20" refString="Millet, L, Malapa, R, Maggia, L, 2012. Diversite genetique des populations de Santalum austrocaledonicum (Santalaceae) au Vanuatu. In: Rapport Final Appel a projet 2008 - Ministere charge de l'Outre-Mer. Institut Agronomique neo-Caledonien &amp; Centre Technique et de Recherche en Agronomie du Vanuatu: 1 - 41" title="Diversite genetique des populations de Santalum austrocaledonicum (Santalaceae) au Vanuatu" volumeTitle="Rapport Final Appel a projet 2008 - Ministere charge de l'Outre-Mer." year="2012">Millet et al. (2012)</bibRefCitation>
on the genetic structure of Vanuatu sandalwood, one for the northern islands and one for the southern islands.
</paragraph>
